BRADSTREET arrived at Schenectady on the 11th of July;
Bradſtreet gives intelligence of the enemy's deſign to attack Oſwego. and the next day acquainted General Abercrombie at Albany of the ſtate of Oſwego.—That he learnt from his priſoners, the French were preparing to attack it, having 1200 men for that purpoſe encamped not far from the eaſternmoſt fort. Upon the receipt of this intelligence, orders were iſſued to Major General Webb, to hold himſelf in readineſs to march for its defence with the 44th regiment. My Lord, Mr. Shirley had, ſeveral days before
